00:45:01.020 --> 00:45:05.620
A week later Menendez assembled a
force of 500 men to march overland

00:45:05.620 --> 00:45:08.550
to attack the French fort.

00:45:08.550 --> 00:45:10.400
It was a bold decision.

00:45:10.400 --> 00:45:14.240
A fierce storm, perhaps a
hurricane battered Menendez's men

00:45:14.240 --> 00:45:19.350
as they made their way north
through marshes and swamps.

00:45:19.350 --> 00:45:23.610 position:56%
Led by two Florida Indians the
Spanish troops reached Fort Caroline

00:45:23.610 --> 00:45:28.860
in the early morning hours
of September 20, 1565.

00:45:28.860 --> 00:45:31.240
Among the first Spaniards
to lead the assault

00:45:31.240 --> 00:45:34.580
on Fort Caroline was Miguel Mora.

00:45:34.580 --> 00:45:37.800
The Spanish victory
was swift and decisive.

00:45:37.800 --> 00:45:41.380
And soon thereafter Menendez
began his ambitious enterprise

00:45:41.380 --> 00:45:44.830
to colonize the American Southeast.

00:45:44.830 --> 00:45:48.150
For Miguel Mora, his
Florida adventure was

00:45:48.150 --> 00:45:51.020
about to take an unexpected turn.

00:45:51.020 --> 00:45:55.630
In 1566 during one of his voyages
along the Florida coast Miguel

00:45:55.630 --> 00:45:58.660
Mora's ship wrecked
in a terrible storm.

00:45:58.660 --> 00:46:01.180
He and several survivors
were taken captive

00:46:01.180 --> 00:46:05.870
by the Tekesta Indians
near present day Miami.

00:46:05.870 --> 00:46:09.530
Mora spent 10 months in captivity.

00:46:09.530 --> 00:46:13.500
&gt;&gt; There I was, naked, no
stockings and fearful for my life.

00:46:13.500 --> 00:46:16.020
Worried that I would be
sacrificed by those Indians.

00:46:16.020 --> 00:46:20.560
Dying of hunger and a captive
for a period of ten months.

00:46:20.560 --> 00:46:21.860
Miguel Mora.

00:46:21.860 --> 00:46:24.580 position:56%
&gt;&gt; J. Michael Francis: After 10
months in captivity Mora and several

00:46:24.580 --> 00:46:27.390 position:56%
of his companions managed to escape.

00:46:27.390 --> 00:46:31.780
He then joined Spanish expeditions
to [inaudible] and Carlos.

00:46:31.780 --> 00:46:34.670
Before returning once
more to Tekesta,

00:46:34.670 --> 00:46:38.150
the site of his 10 month captivity.

00:46:38.150 --> 00:46:42.700
In 1568 the Spanish abandoned the
Takesta settlement along with many

00:46:42.700 --> 00:46:44.750
of the other early garrisons.

00:46:44.750 --> 00:46:49.890
Miguel Mora sailed to
Cuba and then to Spain.

00:46:49.890 --> 00:46:52.440
He would never return to Florida.

00:46:53.450 --> 00:46:57.300
Yet for more than two centuries
after his departure the shoals

00:46:57.300 --> 00:47:01.160
and mouths near present day
Biscayne Bay carried his name.

00:47:01.160 --> 00:47:02.830
The name of a Spanish soldier

00:47:02.830 --> 00:47:08.510 position:56%
in captive whose Florida experiences
have long since been forgotten.

00:47:08.510 --> 00:47:21.850
