00:51:24.860 --> 00:51:27.450
Yes?

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:29.120
&gt;&gt; Why [inaudible]
missions survive in Florida

00:51:29.120 --> 00:51:32.030
like they did in California?

00:51:32.030 --> 00:51:33.890
&gt;&gt; J. Michael Francis: Well
because they built the missions

00:51:33.890 --> 00:51:37.640
from material that didn't
survive over the test of time.

00:51:37.640 --> 00:51:41.070
They were waddle and dob
constructions with thatch roofs.

00:51:41.070 --> 00:51:43.930
And then of course the
main reason why so many

00:51:43.930 --> 00:51:49.170
of the missions don't exist were
they were destroyed by the English

00:51:49.170 --> 00:51:54.420
and their allies as they came in
from the Carolinas and Georgia.

00:51:54.420 --> 00:51:57.500
The early 17th century, late 17th

00:51:57.500 --> 00:52:00.750
and early 18th centuries
those missions were sites

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:04.290
where of massive slave
raiding expeditions

00:52:04.290 --> 00:52:07.430
from English settlements
to the North.

00:52:07.430 --> 00:52:10.160 position:56%
So they were absolutely devastating.

00:52:10.160 --> 00:52:14.880
And so when the Spanish
left Florida in 1764

00:52:14.880 --> 00:52:20.140
when they returned 21 years later
the missions don't come with them.

00:52:20.140 --> 00:52:24.530
That's it, that whole mission
trail that existed starting

00:52:24.530 --> 00:52:29.640
from the earliest established
mission which was 1587.

00:52:29.640 --> 00:52:30.970
Just outside of St. Augustine.

00:52:30.970 --> 00:52:34.450
What is now the Fountain of
Youth Archeological Park.

00:52:34.450 --> 00:52:37.560
And the mission grounds
that are right next to it.

00:52:37.560 --> 00:52:40.560
That is the oldest
established Franciscan mission

00:52:40.560 --> 00:52:44.330
in the continental United States.

00:52:44.330 --> 00:52:49.250
Places like Cumberland Island
had Franciscan missions.

00:52:49.250 --> 00:52:52.600
So the whole story really
goes up the Atlantic seaboard

00:52:52.600 --> 00:52:55.830
and into North Carolina
and what is now Tennessee.

00:52:55.830 --> 00:53:01.200 position:56%
And we think this is a good way to
weave all those narratives together.

00:53:01.200 --> 00:53:05.480
And eventually weave it
into a Jamestown narrative.

