yeah, we want to do something

01:00:38.200 --> 01:00:41.270
like this for Texas,
California, New Spain, Cuba.

01:00:41.270 --> 01:00:46.860
You know the prosopography
it's one of the problems

01:00:46.860 --> 01:00:50.510
with doing prosopography
is it's enormously,

01:00:50.510 --> 01:00:53.780
enormously time consuming.

01:00:53.780 --> 01:00:58.560
And it's not something you'd
really have a doctoral student do

01:00:58.560 --> 01:01:02.310
because unless you wanted
that doctoral student

01:01:02.310 --> 01:01:05.680
to spend 15 years doing
that project.

01:01:05.680 --> 01:01:07.860
But if it were in smaller
parts and we could farm

01:01:07.860 --> 01:01:10.740
out those smaller pieces
then that could work.

01:01:10.740 --> 01:01:14.190
I would love to see the kind of
prosopography that we've done

01:01:14.190 --> 01:01:17.250
for Florida for other
parts of Spanish America.

01:01:17.250 --> 01:01:19.460
And right now it's
really quite limited.

01:01:19.460 --> 01:01:23.080
And especially if you were to
compare it to the work they've done

01:01:23.080 --> 01:01:25.080
in England which is incredible,

01:01:25.080 --> 01:01:28.470
the prosopography for
Anglo Saxon England.

01:01:28.470 --> 01:01:33.050
They're all sorts of incredible
sites on prosopography in England

01:01:33.050 --> 01:01:35.780
because they've spent so
much time working on that.

01:01:35.780 --> 01:01:38.560
And we just don't have the
equivalent for Spanish America yet.

01:01:38.560 --> 01:01:42.630
&gt;&gt; I was going to say
when you say Florida,

01:01:42.630 --> 01:01:46.300
what's your [inaudible] definition.

01:01:46.300 --> 01:01:49.890
I understand West Florida ran
all the way to the Mississippi.

01:01:49.890 --> 01:01:52.250
&gt;&gt; J. Michael Francis: Yes and of
course West Florida doesn't exist

01:01:52.250 --> 01:01:53.780
until after the British arrive.

01:01:53.780 --> 01:01:59.490
So Florida in the 16th century, I'm
taking the very loose definition

01:01:59.490 --> 01:02:01.480
of what the Spanish
refer to as [inaudible]

01:02:01.480 --> 01:02:04.570
which extended all the way
up the Atlantic seaboard.

01:02:04.570 --> 01:02:05.870
You could make a case

01:02:05.870 --> 01:02:09.880
that it included even
Newfoundland even though in many

01:02:09.880 --> 01:02:13.830
of the maps they start to
refer to that area once you get

01:02:13.830 --> 01:02:17.670
up into New England as the
Province of Cod [inaudible].

01:02:17.670 --> 01:02:20.480
And you see the, this is
the land of [inaudible]

01:02:20.480 --> 01:02:23.020
where they would cod fish.

01:02:23.020 --> 01:02:27.100
But the Spanish saw that all as
part of the provinces of Florida

01:02:27.100 --> 01:02:31.670
and it extended into the
interior until you arrived

01:02:31.670 --> 01:02:33.940
at some unknown place

01:02:33.940 --> 01:02:36.160
that eventually marked
what became New Spain.

01:02:36.160 --> 01:02:39.250
&gt;&gt; I was going to say
when you mentioned cod,

01:02:39.250 --> 01:02:42.970
the fisheries attracted
Spanish fishermen

01:02:42.970 --> 01:02:44.750
from an early, early period.

01:02:44.750 --> 01:02:46.400
&gt;&gt; J. Michael Francis:
Oh absolutely.

01:02:46.400 --> 01:02:47.770
&gt;&gt; It was the cod.

01:02:47.770 --> 01:02:49.800
&gt;&gt; J. Michael Francis:
Yea, absolutely.

01:02:49.800 --> 01:02:52.070
In fact it would not
be at all surprising

01:02:52.070 --> 01:02:53.370
if there were cod [inaudible]

01:02:53.370 --> 01:02:55.770
and French cod fishermen before
Columbus fishing off those

01:02:55.770 --> 01:02:57.070
grand banks.

01:02:57.070 --> 01:02:59.000
But, you know, we don't
have the documents for it.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:00.380
They were certainly fishing there

01:03:00.380 --> 01:03:03.350
in the late 15th century
without a doubt.

01:03:03.350 --> 01:03:07.450
And we have the documentation for
that cod fishing in the 1490s.

01:03:07.450 --> 01:03:08.750
So probably before then
they were cod fishing there.

01:03:08.750 --> 01:03:10.360
So yea, so that would be the
definition in the 16th century.

01:03:10.360 --> 01:03:11.770
And then that definition, those
boundaries change over time.

01:03:11.770 --> 01:03:13.450
And so you could do a timeline
for Florida that would mark that.

01:03:13.450 --> 01:03:14.750
You know, you could mark
those geographical divisions.

